## 5. Adding Dependencies in Eclipse (pom.xml)

**Option A — Directly edit pom.xml:**
```xml
<dependencies>
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.seleniumhq.selenium</groupId>
        <artifactId>selenium-java</artifactId>
        <version>4.20.0</version>
    </dependency>
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.testng</groupId>
        <artifactId>testng</artifactId>
        <version>7.10.2</version>
        <scope>test</scope>
    </dependency>
</dependencies>
```
Save the file → Eclipse auto-downloads the JARs from the **Maven Central Repository** into your local `.m2` repository.

**Option B — Via Eclipse UI:**
Right-click project → `Maven` → `Add Dependency` → search artifact name → select → `OK`

**Where to find dependency snippets?**
Go to [mvnrepository.com](https://mvnrepository.com) → search library → copy the `<dependency>` XML block → paste into `pom.xml`.

**To manually refresh dependencies:**
Right-click project → `Maven` → `Update Project` (or `Alt+F5`)

