## 6. Maven Build Lifecycle (Phases)
Maven follows a sequential lifecycle — running a later phase automatically runs all previous ones.

| Phase | Description |
|---|---|
| `validate` | Checks project structure/config is correct |
| `compile` | Compiles the source code |
| `test` | Runs unit tests (via a testing framework like JUnit/TestNG) |
| `package` | Packages compiled code into JAR/WAR |
| `verify` | Runs checks to validate the package is valid |
| `install` | Installs package into local repository (`.m2`) for use in other local projects |
| `deploy` | Copies package to a remote repository for sharing with other teams |

---

## 7. Common Maven Commands

| Command | Usage |
|---|---|
| `mvn -v` | Check Maven & Java version |
| `mvn clean` | Deletes the `target` folder (old build files) |
| `mvn compile` | Compiles the source code |
| `mvn test` | Runs test cases |
| `mvn package` | Builds JAR/WAR file |
| `mvn install` | Installs the build into local `.m2` repo |
| `mvn clean install` | Cleans old build + creates fresh build (most commonly used) |
| `mvn clean test` | Cleans + runs tests only |
| `mvn dependency:tree` | Shows all dependencies (including transitive ones) as a tree |
| `mvn clean install -DskipTests` | Builds project but skips running tests |
| `mvn test -Dtest=ClassName` | Runs a specific test class |
| `mvn -Dmaven.test.failure.ignore=true test` | Continues build even if a test fails |

**Running from Eclipse:**
Right-click project → `Run As` → `Maven build...` → type goal (e.g., `clean install`) in the **Goals** field → `Run`

