## 9. Key pom.xml Elements Summary
```xml
<project>
    <groupId>...</groupId>       <!-- organization/company id -->
    <artifactId>...</artifactId> <!-- project name -->
    <version>...</version>       <!-- project version -->
    <packaging>jar</packaging>   <!-- jar / war / pom -->
    
    <dependencies>...</dependencies>  <!-- external libraries -->
    <build>
        <plugins>...</plugins>        <!-- e.g., compiler plugin, surefire plugin for tests -->
    </build>
</project>
```

---

## 10. Quick Interview-Style Points
- Maven follows the principle of **"Convention over Configuration"** — standard structure, minimal setup.
- Solves **dependency hell** via transitive dependency resolution.
- `mvn clean install` is the most-used command in real projects/CI-CD pipelines.
- Maven integrates well with CI/CD tools (Jenkins) and testing frameworks (TestNG/JUnit) — commonly used in Selenium test automation frameworks.
- Alternative build tools: **Ant** (no dependency management, more manual) and **Gradle** (uses Groovy/Kotlin DSL, faster builds, more flexible than Maven).
